<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-3969] Splitting starts counting for cutting out pages wrongly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3969</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now the usage of &apos;splitAtPage&apos; is wrong. Let&apos;s assume there is a document with 1000pages,&lt;br/&gt;
startPage=238, endPage=977, splitAtPage=17 then pdfbox starts splitAtPage at page #0! This leads to the following&lt;br/&gt;
groups: 1, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17,&lt;br/&gt;
17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would have expected: 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17,&lt;br/&gt;
17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 17, 9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This does not allow for example cutting out some parts of a document.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
